{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb84602a8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1320b–4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1320b–4"},"text":"§ 1320b–4.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Nonprofit hospital or critical access hospital philanthropy","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of determining, under subchapters XVIII and XIX of this chapter, the reasonable costs of services provided by nonprofit hospitals or critical access hospitals, the following items shall not be deducted from the operating costs of such hospitals or critical access hospitals:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb84602a9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1320b–4/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A grant, gift, or endowment, or income therefrom, which is to or for such a hospital and which has not been designated by the donor for paying any specific operating costs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb84602aa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1320b–4/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A grant or similar payment which is to such a hospital, which was made by a governmental entity, and which is not available under the terms of the grant or payment for use as operating funds.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb84602ab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1320b–4/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Those types of donor designated grants and gifts (including grants and similar payments which are made by a governmental entity), and income therefrom, which the Secretary determines, in the best interests of needed health care, should be encouraged.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb84602ac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1320b–4/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The proceeds from the sale or mortgage of any real estate or other capital asset of such a hospital, which real estate or asset the hospital acquired through gift or grant, if such proceeds are not available for use as operating funds under the terms of the gift or grant.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Paragraph (4) shall not apply to the recovery of the appropriate share of depreciation when gains or losses are realized from the disposal of depreciable assets.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb84602ad-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title XI, § 1134, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/499/tIX/s901/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–499, title IX, § 901(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-05"},"text":"Dec. 5, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2611"},"text":"94 Stat. 2611","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXXI/s2193/c/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XXI, § 2193(c)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/827"},"text":"95 Stat. 827","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248/tI/s137/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248, title I, § 137(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-03"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/377"},"text":"96 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/tVI/s6003/g/3/D/iii"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, title VI, § 6003(g)(3)(D)(iii)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2153"},"text":"103 Stat. 2153","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/tIV/s4201/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, title IV, § 4201(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/373"},"text":"111 Stat. 373","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb84602ae-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb84602af-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb84602b0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":" substituted “critical access” for “rural primary care” in two places in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239","children":[],"tail":" substituted “hospitals or rural primary care hospitals” for “hospitals” in two places in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Par. (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":" substituted “sale” for “scale”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35","children":[],"tail":" substituted “subchapters XVIII and” for “subchapters V, XVIII, and” in provision preceding par. (1)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb84602b1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb84602b2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1997 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":" applicable to services furnished on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1997","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s4201/d"},"text":"section 4201(d) of Pub. L. 105–33","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1395f"},"text":"section 1395f of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb84602b3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1982 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl